<statement>
<p>Suppose enrollment in a class was 79 in the fall and 54 in the following spring.</p>
<p>It was a <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 2" class="text"/> percent </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>decrease</li> 
<li>increase</li> 
</ol></p>



</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>32</li><li>A: decrease</li></ul></p><p>Because 79 is bigger than 54 it is a percent decrease.</p>
<p>The percent decrease is <m>\displaystyle{100}{\left(\frac{{{79}-{54}}}{{79}}\right)}={100}\cdot\frac{{25}}{{79}}\approx{32}\%</m>.</p>
</solution>
